net.hudup.core.logistic

Class UriAssocDefault

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.logistic.UriAssocAbstract
      • net.hudup.core.logistic.UriAssocDefault
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, UriAssoc

    public class UriAssocDefault
extends UriAssocAbstract
    This class is default implementation of the interface UriAssoc. In other words, it is the default URI associator. In current implementation, UriAssocDefault uses the programming library TrueZip for processing on file system, compressed file, HTTP. TrueZip is developed by Schlichtherle IT Services, available at https://christian-schlichtherle.bitbucket.io/truezip
    Version:
    11.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

      • chooseUri

        public xURI chooseUri(java.awt.Component comp,
                      boolean open,
                      java.lang.String[] exts,
                      java.lang.String[] descs,
                      xURI curStore)
        Description copied from interface: UriAssoc
        This method shows a graphic user interface (GUI) allowing users to select object (archive-file, store-directory) they want. Such GUI is called choice dialog. Such chosen object is returned by its referred URI.
        Parameters:
        comp - The graphic user interface (GUI) component works as a parent component of choice dialog.
        open - If true then, choice dialog is open dialog allowing users to choose and open files. Otherwise, choice dialog is save dialog allowing users to choose and save objects.
        exts - The specified array of archive (file) extensions which are used to filter objects that users select, for example, "*.hdp", "*.xls". Each extension has a description. The respective array of extension descriptions is specified by the parameter descs.
        descs - The specified array of descriptions, for example, "Hudup file", "Excel 97-2003". Note that each extension has a description and the respective array of file extensions is represented by the parameter exts.
        curStore - Current store (directory) to open choice dialog
        Returns:
        URI represented by xURI of chosen object.
